    "narrative": "Ghost Ride the WHIP is positioned for a high-ceiling output today, headlined by the leadoff spark of **James Wood** (75.94) and the favorable platoon/park combination for **Mickey Moniak** (75.75). **Wood** benefits from an elite matchup against a weak starter, while **Moniak** is our premier play, leveraging a +14% park factor and a substantial platoon advantage to maximize scoring potential. **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** (75.72) also stands out as a core staple; his score is buoyed by a strong SP skill matchup and elite sprint speed, which remains our primary weapon to combat the scarcity of stolen bases in this 5x5 format. While **Corbin Carroll** (64.19) and **Giancarlo Stanton** (66.92) face slightly tougher individual conditions, both maintain strong efficiency scores and are locked in as high-upside starters.\n\nThe lineup construction prioritizes efficiency over raw power, forcing difficult sits on our depth chart. **Alex Freeland** (46.07) was the toughest exclusion; despite his strong BvP historicals (56 PA), the sheer difficulty of facing a high-level arm like Cease suppressed his efficiency below our starting threshold. We are also monitoring the risk associated with **Vinnie Pasquantino** (48.67) and **Gabriel Moreno** (52.07), both of whom are dealing with dynamic platoon disadvantages against southpaws; while they remain in the lineup due to the lack of better internal options, their production is more fragile today. We must also exercise caution with **Trevor Story** (67.62); despite a massive SP xERA advantage, the \"Wind In\" warning could deflate his power metrics, necessitating a close watch as the game progresses. With **Josh Naylor** and **Jose Caballero** unavailable, the current configuration is our most optimized path to winning the week.",
